[{"location":"api/#FiberNlse-API","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Modules = [FiberNlse]\nOrder   = [:function, :type]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.dispersion-Tuple{Float64, Float64}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.dispersion","text":"dispersion(D::Float64, λ::Float64)\n\nGenerates the Dispersion structure for a fiber\n- D : dispersion factor in s/m²\n- λ : central wavelength of the study in m\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.dispersion-Tuple{Float64}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.dispersion","text":"dispersion(β::Float64)\n\nGenerates the Dispersion structure for a fiber\n- β : second derivative of the propagation constants\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.dispersion-Tuple{Vector{Float64}}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.dispersion","text":"dispersion(β::Vector{Float64})\n\nGenerates the Dispersion structure for a fiber\n- β : nth derivative of the propagation constants from 2 to n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.edfa-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.edfa","text":"edfa(L::Float64, G::Float64, λ::Float64)\n\nGenerates a fiber of length L [m] and gain G [dB] arround a wavelength of λ [m]\n\nSee also : (smf28)[@ref smf28]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.input-Tuple{Field}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.input","text":"input(f::Field)\n\nreturns the signal at the beginning of the propagation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.output-Tuple{Field}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.output","text":"output(f::Field)\n\nreturns the signal at the end of the propagation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.smf28-Tuple{Float64, Float64}","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.smf28","text":"smf28(L::Float64, λ::Float64)\n\nGenerates a standard monomode fiber (smf28) of length L [m] arround a wavelength of λ [m]\n\nSee also : (edfa)[@ref edfa]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.Dispersion","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.Dispersion","text":"Dispersion(β::Union{Float64,Vector{Float64}})\n\nStructure containing dispersion caracteristics for the fiber\n\nCan contain the dispersion only (second derivative of the propagation constant) or a list of slopes from second order to nth order\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.Fiber","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.Fiber","text":"Fiber(L::Float64, D::Dispersion, γ::Float64, α::Float64)\n\nStructure containing fiber caracteristics :\n- L : length in [m]\n- D : (dispersion)[@ref Dispersion]\n- γ : nonlinear factor in [1 / W / m]\n- α : fiber attenuation or gain (exponential) in [1 / m]\n\nSee also : (smf28)[@ref smf28], (edfa)[@ref edfa]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#FiberNlse.Field","page":"API","title":"FiberNlse.Field","text":"Field(ψ::Matrix{ComplexF64}, l::Vector{Float64}, t::Vector{Float64})\n\nStructure containing space/time data resulting from the simulation\n- ψ : The signal propagation matrix\n- l : The space vector in m\n- t : The time vector in s\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"theory/#Theory","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Theory","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Kerr-nonlinearity-in-fibers","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Kerr nonlinearity in fibers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Physical-origins","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Physical origins","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Effects","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Effects","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Self-phase-modulation","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Self-phase modulation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Four-wave-mixing","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Four-wave mixing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Modelization","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Modelization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"theory/#Non-linear-Schrödinger-Equation-(NLSE)","page":"Theoretical Background","title":"Non-linear Schrödinger Equation (NLSE)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/dispersion/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"EditURL = \"https://github.com/curio-sitas/FiberNlse.jl/blob/main/docs/examples/dispersion.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/dispersion/#Dispersion-in-optical-fibers","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/dispersion/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"#TODO","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/dispersion/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/dispersion/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/spm/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"EditURL = \"https://github.com/curio-sitas/FiberNlse.jl/blob/main/docs/examples/spm.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/spm/#Dispersion-in-optical-fibers","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/spm/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"#TODO","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/spm/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/spm/","page":"Dispersion in optical fibers","title":"Dispersion in optical fibers","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"userguide/#Principle","page":"User Guide","title":"Principle","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"userguide/#Defining-propagation-medium","page":"User Guide","title":"Defining propagation medium","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"userguide/#Fiber","page":"User Guide","title":"Fiber","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"userguide/#Dispersion","page":"User Guide","title":"Dispersion","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"userguide/#Defining-an-input-signal","page":"User Guide","title":"Defining an input signal","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"userguide/#Running-the-simulation","page":"User Guide","title":"Running the simulation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"userguide/#Analyze,-plot-the-output","page":"User Guide","title":"Analyze, plot the output","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#FiberNlse.jl","page":"Home","title":"FiberNlse.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#What-is-it-?","page":"Home","title":"What is it ?","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"It is a Fourier Split-Step based algorithm which solves the Non-Linear Schrödinger Equation(NLSE). It uses as parameters the usual quantities describing optical fibers and optical signal.","category":"page"},{"location":"#To-do-what-?","page":"Home","title":"To do what ?","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The package is designed for photonic researchers using optical fibers who need to simulate the propagation of an optical signal in such a medium. It can be used to study the evolution of a pulse train or the degradation of a transmission line by dispersion and nonlinearities.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The package currently supports :     * Kerr nonlinearity     * Linear losses/gain     * Optical envelope (SVEA)     * Self-steepening     * Dispersion (from order 2 to n)","category":"page"},{"location":"#How-to-use-it-?","page":"Home","title":"How to use it ?","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You will learn to use the packages by reading the user guide and the examples","category":"page"},{"location":"#Roadmap","page":"Home","title":"Roadmap","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In the future, the plan is to implement :     * Raman scattering (intra-pulse)     * Brillouin scattering     * Polarisation (PMD)     * Random sequence generator and BER tests/ Eye diagram","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/soliton/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"EditURL = \"https://github.com/curio-sitas/FiberNlse.jl/blob/main/docs/examples/soliton.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/soliton/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/soliton/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"}]
